issuetype.description: Issue Investigations are opened after a test run fails. These tickets track the work required to determine if the test failure should lead to a Defect. Issue Investigations were introduced as part of the RQM-JIRA integration and should be used for RQM test run failures.
issuetype.name: Issue Investigation

fields.customfield_22000:
Evaluate the questions on the Prioritize Change Requests wiki page under the Evaluate Development Issues section, to determine whether the combination of any previously existing defects and the new defects increases or adds new risks not previously identified.

If the answer to any of the Risk and Compliance Review questions is Yes, review and, if necessary, update the Release Justification text area on this Risk Assessment tab with the justification to release the software. If all answers are No, update the Release Justification text area on this Risk Assessment tab with "No risk".

Prioritize Change Requests - ProcessIT - Cerner Wiki

Hi Srikanth.
We've confirmed that the same issue does not occur on all midtiers. 
{color:#000000}BSSWUK72405{color} is unaffected

{color:#000000}BSSWUK72403{color} is affected, PC name: PC11161

 

[^logs.zip]

Hi Srikanth. I copied the IND preferences from the working midtiers and this is resolved now, thank you.
Are there any other required preference rows which may be missing please? J

I don't think we have any required preferences. it is based on the client's preference. if they think they are not seeing the tab or other preference they can select it from the admin tool.

I am going to close this Jira, feel free to create a new Jira if you need more help. Thank you!
